# n8n Webhook authentication

Whenever creating an n8n Webhook node, it MUST use Header Auth.

- Set `parameters.authentication: "headerAuth"` on the Webhook node.
- Attach an `httpHeaderAuth` credential via the node's `credentials` field, e.g.

```json
{
  "parameters": { "authentication": "headerAuth", "httpMethod": "POST", "path": "..." },
  "credentials": {
    "httpHeaderAuth": { "id": "<credentialId>", "name": "<credentialName>" }
  }
}
```

## Reusing existing credentials

- The n8n public API does NOT allow listing/reading credentials
  (`n8n_manage_credentials` with `action: "list"` returns `Forbidden`).
  Only `create`, `delete`, and `getSchema` work.
- Known credential IDs are tracked in `n8n/n8n-credential.md`.
- BEFORE creating any Webhook node, ASK the user whether to reuse an existing
  credential listed in `n8n/n8n-credential.md` or provide a new one.
- When the user provides a new credential ID, append it to
  `n8n/n8n-credential.md`.
- Only create a new `httpHeaderAuth` credential when the user confirms none
  exists. Schema fields: `name` (header name) and `value` (header value).
